 Phumalanga police on Thursday destroyed  50 bags of dagga that was seized back in 2016. "During the month of October 2016, Phumalanga SAPS members arrested  a suspect driving a motor vehicle  carrying 50 bags of dagga," said police spokesperson, W/ O Moitheri Bojabotseha. "The case was finalised this year in March 2018." He said that the accused was sentenced to pay a fine of R10 000. "In terms of the law when a case  has been  finalised the  dagga must be destroyed." Cluster Commander, Brigadier Xakavu, then oversaw the destruction of the dagga. 